      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM BOBBY (1) is a talented trotter resuming. He was taking on strong company at the end of last campaign and had some tough draws so was far from disgraced. Yet to win fresh but has placed multiple times and he is well served by the ace draw. LOVEMETO NZ (4) is racing well having recorded a win and two placings from his last three starts, all from tough barriers. Owns a handy record at this circuit and distance including a Group 1 second to wonder mare Keayang Zahara earlier in the year and has the fitness edge on the top pick. REMUS PHOENIX (7) draws wide but deserved his last-start win on the back off some consistent form. Could go on with it. QUIRKY CHARACTER (9) overcame a wide draw for a win here a fortnight ago, adding to a good record at this circuit and distance. May need a touch of luck from this barrier but deserves respect as does ALDEBARAN ACRUX (8) who draws for a trail and comes off a placing in a Group 1 for the mares in Sydney last start.",
